@startuml
title WorkMesh Application Architecture Overview

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam ArrowColor #222222
skinparam PackageBorderColor #222222
skinparam PackageBackgroundColor #F7F7F7
skinparam ComponentBorderColor #222222
skinparam ComponentBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam DatabaseBorderColor #222222
skinparam DatabaseBackgroundColor #FFF9DB
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FFF9DB
skinparam NoteBorderColor #D09B2C
left to right direction

actor "Developer / Agent" as User
component "workmesh\nCLI adapter" as CLI
component "workmesh-mcp\nstdio wrapper" as MCP
component "workmesh-mcp-server\nMCP adapter" as MCPS
component "workmesh-tools\nshared tool contract" as TOOLS
component "workmesh-core\ndomain + storage logic" as CORE
component "workmesh-render\nrender providers" as RENDER

database "Repo-local state\ntasks/\n.workmesh/context.json\n.workmesh/truth/" as REPO
database "Global state\n~/.workmesh/sessions\n~/.workmesh/worktrees" as GLOBAL

User --> CLI : local commands
User --> MCP : MCP stdio session
MCP --> MCPS : tool call transport
CLI --> TOOLS : tool metadata\nparity helpers
MCPS --> TOOLS : tool metadata\nresponse policy
CLI --> CORE : direct domain commands
MCPS --> CORE : execute tool actions
CLI --> RENDER : render fallback
MCPS --> RENDER : render_* tools
TOOLS --> CORE : shared resolution\nand helper flows
CORE --> REPO : repo-local persistence
CORE --> GLOBAL : global continuity\nand worktree state

note bottom of TOOLS
Shared layer for tool metadata,
response shaping, and adapter-neutral
resolution helpers.
end note

note bottom of CORE
Business rules, locking, validation,
truth/session/workstream/worktree state.
end note

@enduml
